results.name: Zsigmondy numbers for a = 5, b = 3: Zs(n, 5, 3) is the greatest divisor of 5^n - 3^n (A005058) that is relatively prime to 5^m - 3^m for all positive integers m < n.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Zsigmondy's Theorem
program: lista(nn) = {prad = 1; for (n=1, nn, val = 5^n-3^n; d = divisors(val); gd = 1; forstep(k=#d, 1, -1, if (gcd(d[k], prad) == 1, g = d[k]; break)); print1(g, ", "); prad = ra(prad*val););} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Nov 15 2016
